    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-24T18:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-24T18:36:00-05:00" n="1108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1108">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4007.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-24T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1912—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Zapata has by letter announced to Consul General Shanklin his intention to attack
                    the City of Mexico and asks that Americans be <pb facs="0928" n="812"
                        xml:id="pg_812"/> advised in order to remove from the city. I desire the
                    Department’s instructions, and meantime have instructed the Consul General to
                    make no reply to Zapata.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
